short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Understand Search Engine Reports. show Canonical link, meta description and title for current page fast. Get more organic traffic.

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
This tool helps you see the canonical link for any page fast.

We added title and meta description support upon user request.

And it also helps you compare search engine results pages between sites or keywords.  It currently compares to the zillow.com site but let us know if you want to compare any two sites or keywords.

The comparison does the following:

Compare Google Search Engine Results Page Between Two Different Sites
To compare Google search engine results page (SERP) between two different sites, you can follow these steps:

Go to Google and enter your search query.
Click on the "Search" button.
Copy the URL of the SERP.
Repeat steps 1-3 for the second site.
Paste the URLs of both SERPs into a diff checker tool.
The diff checker tool will highlight the differences between the two SERPs.
Here are some things to look for when comparing SERPs:

The number of results returned.
The order of the results.
The titles and descriptions of the results.
The URLs of the results.
The snippets of the results.
